olive oil
1 tomato
½ tin sweetcorn
2 clove garlic
1 packet ciabatta
30 g butter
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend

• Roughly chop tomato. Drain sweetcorn (see ingredients). Finely chop
garlic. Cut or tear ciabatta into bite-sized chunks.

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high
heat.
• Cook ciabatta until golden and slightly crisp, 5-6 minutes.
• Add the butter and garlic and cook, tossing, until fragrant, 1 minute.
Season to taste, then transfer to a large bowl.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is
hot, cook diced chicken, sweetcorn and Louisiana spice blend, tossing
occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Set aside.
• Meanwhile, add mixed leaves, tomato and a drizzle of white wine vinegar
and olive oil to the bowl with croutons. Season to taste.

• Divide garlic crouton salad between bowls.
• Top with Louisiana chicken and charred corn.
• Drizzle over smokey aioli to serve. Enjoy!